description: An Evening in Paris Is A Bollywood Romantic Thriller Hindi Movie, Directed By Shakti Samanta, Starring Shammi Kapoor, Sharmila Tagore, Pran and Rajendra Nath In The Lead Roles. Deepa Goes To Paris To Find Love, And She Meets Shyam, An Amiable Gentleman. However, Since Shekhar Needs To Marry Her In Order To Clear His Debts, He Replaces Deepa With Her Lookalike.

title: I Want You
cast: Dana Andrews, Dorothy McGuire, Farley Granger
description: In 1950, small-town Americans try to deal with military conscription.

title: The Mimic
cast: Thomas Sadoski, Jake Robinson, Austin Pendleton, Gina Gershon, Jessica Walter, Marilu Henner, Didi Conn, Tammy Blanchard, M. Emmet Walsh, Doug Plaut, Josh Pais, Steve Routman, Matthew Maher, Jessica Keenan Wynn, Teddy Coluca
description: A screenwriter (Thomas Sadoski) explores the lighter side of a sociopath when he befriends a new neighbor (Jake Robinson) on the local newspaper. After unsettling rendezvous, he sets out to learn his true intentions.

title: Relaxer
cast: Joshua Burge, David Dastmalchian, Andrew Hyland, Mahfuz Rahman, Madi Bachman, Adina Howard, Amari Cheatom, Jeen Na
description: Doom and gloom are on the way. The Y2K apocalypse can't be stopped. Abbie's older brother issues him the ultimate challenge before it goes down: beat the infamous level 256 in Pac-Man and no getting up from the couch until he does so. Abbie's survival story begins here; inside a rotting living room with no food or water, and a revolving door of numb-nut friends and acquaintances.

title: Detour
cast: Tom Neal, Ann Savage, Edmund MacDonald, Claudia Drake
description: A nightclub pianist (Tom Neal) hitchhikes to join his girl in LA. When the sleazy gambler he's riding with mysteriously dies; he takes the man's identity. But thanks to a blackmailing dame (Ann Savage) his every move plunges him deeper into trouble.

title: Chutney Popcorn
cast: Nisha Ganatra, Jill Hennessy, Madhur Jaffrey, Sakina Jaffrey, Cara Buono, Nick Chinlund
description: A woman. Her girlfriend. A sister. Her husband. Their baby.

title: Bunty Aur Babli
cast: Abhishek Bachchan, Rani Mukerji, Amitabh Bachchan, Aishwarya Rai Bachchan, Kiran Juneja, Puneet Issar
description: Rakesh (Abhishek Bachchan) is a man of schemes, ideas, invention and restlessness. Small town girl, Vimmi (Rani Mukerji) doesn’t want to become just another marriageable girl. Somewhere along their individual journey, they meet and in a moment of mistaken truth, the legend of Bunty and Babli is born. We follow the duo gig after gig, hiding from an upset policeman, Dashrath Singh (Amitabh Bachchan)

title: Brotherhood
cast: Brendan Fehr, Brendan Fletcher, Jake Manley, Dylan Everett
description: In 1926, a band of teenage boys arrive at Long Point Camp for the adventure of their lives. When their canoe capsizes in a freak summer storm, their holiday descends into a soul-shuddering fight for survival.

title: Anari
cast: Venkatesh Daggubati, Karisma Kapoor, Johnny Lever, Rakhee Gulzar, Suresh Oberoi, Gulshan Grover, Laxmikant Berde, Priya Arun, Beena Banerjee, Adi Irani, Shashi Kiran, Sudha Rani, Raju Shrestha, Subbiraj
description: A rich girl appoints a simpleton, as her bodyguard. She soon falls in love with him, which creates havoc in his life.

title: The Surrogacy Trap
cast: Mia Kirchner, Natalie Brown, Rachel Blanchard, David Julian Hirsh, Emma Campbell
description: After losing hope of conceiving a child on their own, Christy and Mitch turn to surrogacy in hopes of creating the perfect family. However, their confidence is quickly shaken when they discover that the young woman might not be as perfect as they first thought.

title: The Believer
cast: Sophie Kargma, Aidan Bristo, Billy Zane, Susan Wilder, Lindsey Ginter
description: Lucas suspects his wife is losing her mind when she claims demons are waging a war in their urban home. Eerie evidence is mounting that she may not actually be crazy after all, but what she's about to tell him next is that he must do the unthinkable.

title: Kaakha Kaakha
cast: Suriya, Jyothika, Jeevan, Daniel Balaji, Devadarshini, Gautham Menon
description: ACP Anbuselvan succeeds in killing a dreaded gangster but Pandya, the gangster's brother, kills Maya, Anbuselvan's wife. Later, Anbuselvan goes all out to finish Pandya and his gang.

title: Guerrilla: The Taking of Patty Hearst
cast: Russ Little, Patty Hearst
description: The Symbionese Liberation Army (SLA). The SLA wreaked havoc on the West Coast and our national psyche, leaving behind a rich trove of paranoid recordings and scores of violent acts, including the kidnapping of heiress Patty Hearst who would subsequently join the SLA under the alias "Tania."

title: Evocateur: The Morton Downey Jr. Movie
director: Seth Kramer, Daniel A. Miller, Jeremy Newberger
cast: Morton Downey Jr
description: Rude, crude and beyond outrageous, Morton Downey Jr. was the profane right-wing prince of the talk show with fistfights, a rabid audience and a mouth that wouldn't quit. Today's extreme tv looks tame by comparison.

title: Ambush at Dark Canyon
cast: Kix Brooks, Ernie Hudson, Abraham Benrubi, Timothy V. Murphy
description: Duke Donovan, a famous lawman turned bank robber, plans a daring escape from prison with help from an old buffalo soldier. If he cannot break out, his ex-partner will murder his wife and ruin the legacy of the U.S. Marshals.

title: The Legend of Lizzie Borden
cast: Elizabeth Montgomery
description: Elizabeth Montgomery stars as Lizzie Borden, a 19th-century Massachusetts woman who is put on trial for the brutal slaughter of her father and stepmother in their family home. She is accused of hacking up her parents with an axe after carefully removing her clothes to avoid bloodstains.

title: First Signal
cast: Paul Noonan, Conor Timmis, Wendy Hartman, Patience McStravick, Stephanie Eaton
description: When Air Force Space Command receives a signal from an alien satellite in Earth orbit an emergency meeting with the President reveals a government conspiracy.

title: White God
cast: Zsófia Psotta, Luke & Body, Sándor Zsótér, Szabolcs Thuróczy, Lili Monori, László Gálffi, Lili Horváth
description: Lili is forced to give up her dog Hagen because its mixed-breed is deemed "unfit" by The State. She and the dog begin a journey back to each other, while all of the "unfit" dogs rise up under a new leader, Hagen.

title: Results
cast: Guy Pearce, Cobie Smulders, Kevin Corrigan, Giovanni Ribisi, Anthony Michael Hall, Brooklyn Decker, Constance Zimmer
description: Divorced, rich, and utterly miserable, Danny [Kevin Corrigan] goes to the local gym, where he meets guru/owner Trevor [Guy Pearce] and irresistibly caustic trainer Kat [Cobie Smulders]. Their three lives are knotted, both professional and personally.

title: Ms. White Light
cast: Roberta Colindrez, Zachary Spicer, John Ortiz, Judith Light
description: Lex Cordova, is a young woman who counsels terminally ill clients that have trouble letting go. While proving uniquely talented in her ability to connect with the dying, Lex is at a total loss when it comes to dealing with everyone else.

title: The Good Catholic
cast: Zachary Spicer, Wrenn Schmidt, Danny Glover, John C. McGinley
description: A young priest’s faith is tested when he finds himself attracted to a woman he meets at confession and his ideals are shaken to the core.

title: Jolt
cast: KATE BECKINSALE, JAI COURTNEY, STANLEY TUCCI, BOBBY CANNAVALE, LAVERNE COX, CONSTANTINE GREGORY, ORI PFEFFER, DAVID BRADLEY, SUSAN SARANDON, LEWIS BRAYNATHAN, COOPER JOSEPH GROGAN, SOPHIE SANDERSON, STEVEN OSBORNE, TOM XANDER, EVAN SHARP, SAVVY CLEMENT, SIMON BULLOK, HARRY ANICHKIN, BRAYDEN PINDUR, LILI RICH, CHLOE RAHAL, CHLOE SARBIB, MARA CHAPANOVA, JAMES GROGAN, ADAM BRASHAW, CHRISTIAN BRASSINGTON, VASIL YORDANOV, EUGENE BUICA, JENNIFER SNODGRASS, GENADIY GANCHEV
description: A bouncer with a slightly murderous anger-management problem that she controls with the help of an electrode-lined vest she uses to shock herself back to normalcy whenever she gets homicidal. After the first guy she's ever fallen for is murdered, she goes on a revenge-fueled rampage to find the killer while the cops pursue her as their chief suspect.

title: Thunderbird 6
cast: Peter Dyneley, Sylvia Anderson, Shane Rimmer, Jeremy Wilkin, Matt Zimmerman, David Graham
description: Those world-famous electronic puppets The International Rescue Team are back with excitement, mystery and thrills ahead after they are faced with a plot to steal their fabulous fleet of rescue planes.

title: A Sunburnt Christmas
cast: Daniel Henshall, Sullivan Stapleton
description: On an outback farm ravaged by drought, the lives of a struggling family are upended when a runaway criminal dressed as Santa Claus crashes onto their property and a wily teenager seizes the opportunity to save the farm and put her fractured family back together.

title: The German Doctor
cast: Alex Brendemühl, Natalia Oreiro, Diego Peretti, Elena Roger, Guillermo Pfening, Florencia Bado
description: Patagonia, 1960. A German doctor meets an Argentinean family and follows them on a long desert road to a small town where the family will be starting a new life. Eva, Enzo and their three children welcome the doctor into their home and entrust their young daughter, Lilith, to his care, not knowing that they are harboring one of the most dangerous criminals in the world.

title: M.O.M. Mothers of Monsters
cast: Melinda Page Hamilton, Ed Asner, Bailey Edwards
description: A distraught mother suspects her teenage son is a psychopath who may shoot up his high school, but when he outsmarts the system, she is forced to take matters into her own hands.

title: Little John
cast: Bentley Mitchum, Jyothika, Anupam Kher, Nassar, Prakash Raj
description: When a visiting researcher tries desperately to escape, after mistakenly captured by police for an alleged theft in a temple, bizarre things start happening.

title: Hoodman
cast: Madison Spear, Brock Morse, Jack James, Skye Roberts, Claire Montgomery
description: An urban legend haunts a small town as a troubled young woman (Madison Spear) seeks to find her missing child. A relentless detective (Brock Morse) pieces together clues that lead them both to a suspected killer (Jack James).

title: Debug
cast: Jason Momoa, Tenika Davis, Adrian Holmes, Kjartan Hewitt
description: Deep space, six young hackers on a grueling work release program attempt to clear out debug, the computer systems of a massive derelict freighter. They quickly fall prey to the ship's artificial intelligence, a program that would kill to be human. As the fractious team is forced to match wits with this rogue program, they discover that the ship holds a deadly secret, and a fate worse than death.

title: Capone
cast: Tom Hardy, Linda Cardellini, Matt Dillon, Kyle MacLachlan
description: A ruthless businessman and bootlegger who ruled Chicago with an iron fist, Al "Fonzo" Capone (Tom Hardy) was the most infamous and feared gangster of American lore. At the age of 47, following nearly a decade of imprisonment, dementia rots Capone's mind and his past becomes present as harrowing memories of his violent and brutal origins melt into his waking life.

title: The Stalker
cast: Troy Fromin, Matthew Ewald, Jimmy Ace Lewis, J Gaven Wilde, Tristan Dye, Chad Ayers, Virginia Vogt
description: The man only known as the Stalker, is looking for the Hamilton's, and is willing to kill anyone who gets in his way. Embark on this horror, mystery, thrill ride, that takes you back to the classic horror films of the 80's.

title: Martin Lawrence Live: Runteldat
cast: Martin Lawrence
description: Lawrence trains his sights on such explosive subjects as parenting, sex and smoking, and, in perhaps the film's most revealing and most powerful section, sets the record straight on his infamous brushes with the law.

title: Jamesy Boy
cast: Mary-Louise Parker, Ving Rhames, James Woods, Taissa Farmiga, Spencer Lofranco
description: Rage-filled teenager James is never one to back down from a fight. He jumps at the chance to run drugs and guns for a gang and quickly ends up behind bars. He turns his life around in prison thanks to the unexpected friendship he forms with a convicted murderer.

title: Camino
cast: Zoë Bell, Nacho Vigalondo, Francisco Barreiro, Sheila Vand, Tenoch Huerta, Dominic Rains, Kevin Pollak
description: In the jungles of Colombia, a photojournalist captures the truth behind a group of missionaries who may not be what they seem.

title: McCanick
cast: Cory Monteith, David Morse, Mike Vogel, Rachel Nichols
description: Set over the course of one day, a narcotics detective hunts for a seemingly harmless young criminal who knows a truth about the cop's past.

title: At the Fork
cast: John Papola, Lisa Versaci, Kim Sturla, Jayson Lusk, Temple Grandin, Malcolm DeKryger
description: Filmmaker and omnivore John Papola and his vegetarian wife Lisa give a timely, unbiased look at how farm animals are raised for consumption. With unprecedented access to large-scale conventional farms, Papola asks the tough questions behind every hamburger, glass of milk and baby-back rib.

title: Age of Heroes
cast: Sean Bean, Danny Dyer, Aksel Hennie
description: The true story of the formation of Ian Fleming's 30 Commando unit, a precursor for the elite forces in the U.K.

title: In the Blink of an Eye
cast: Jeffrey Dean Morgan, Denise Richards, Mimi Rogers, Piper Laurie, Veronica Hamel, Kevin Rahm
description: A filmmaker learns about her childhood friend who has been jailed in connection to the shooting deaths of two police officers. Her friend says she didn't commit the murders, but has ultimately been sentenced to death. Putting her career on hold, the filmmaker endeavors to win freedom for her friend and prove her innocence. Based on a true story.

title: The Misadventures of Mistress Maneater
cast: Lorrisa Julianus, Mickey O'Sullivan, Shannon Brown, Cynda Williams, Bonnie Morgan, Molly Morgan, Robyn Coffin, John Mossman, Adam Christopher
description: With only 30 days to repay a massive loan, a disgraced art historian is forced into a scandalous scheme: win the heart of, and then extort, the Episcopal priest avoiding her like loose glitter. When she discovers him hiding the world's greatest lost masterpiece, will she betray the heroic man who believes in her genius, or fall for him and doom herself to a custom pair of concrete stilettos?

title: The Absent
cast: Ariadna Gil, Jordi Mollá
description: Julia and Samuel move with the children to a housing estate in the suburbs of the city. It seems like the ideal place, but Julia will soon discover that she hides something strange because the urbanization is completely deserted. She is terrified by the situation and puzzled by the indifference of Samuel and the children, she begins to suspect that she is the victim of a dark conspiracy.

title: Savannah
cast: Jim Caviezel, Chiwetel Ejiofor, Jaimie Alexander, Sam Shepard
description: Drama about the friendship between an Oxford-educated Southerner and a former black slave in turn-of-the-century Savannah.

title: Beyond the Woods
cast: John Ryan Howard, Irene Kelleher
description: Seven friends go to a holiday home in a forest in Ireland. A sinkhole has opened nearby and is spewing hot sulphur. The friends start acting out of character and soon come to realize that something evil is also crossing through from another dimension.

title: Whitey: United States of America v. James J. Bulger
cast: James J. Bulger,  Jr.
description: The true story of Whitey Bulger, inspiration for Jack Nicolson's character in Martin Scorsese's THE DEPARTED. Acclaimed documentarian Joe Berlinger lays bare the real story of the South Boston crime boss, including his sensational trial. Key players on every side reveal Bulger's influence on crime and law enforcement.

title: Extremely Wicked, Shockingly Evil and Vile
cast: Zac Efron, Lily Collins, Kaya Scodelario, Jeffrey Donovan, Angela Sarafyan, Jim Parsons, John Malkovich, Haley Joel Osment, Dylan Baker, Brian Geraghty
description: Single mother Liz falls for Ted Bundy and refuses to believe the truth about his crimes for years. A drama based on a true story.

title: The Masked Saint
cast: Brett Granstaff, Lara Jean Chorostecki, Diahann Carroll, Roddy Piper, James Preston Rogers, Mykel Shannon Jenkins, Patrick McKenna
description: Inspired by true events. Professional wrestler Chris Samuels retires from the ring and settles down as a pastor by day. By night, he confronts injustice as a masked vigilante. When the worlds collide, he must reconcile these very separate lives.

title: The Little Death
cast: Josh Lawson, Bojana Novakovic, Damon Herriman, Kate Mulvany, Kate Box, Patrick Brammall, Alan Dukes, Lisa McCune, Erin James, TJ Power, Kim Gyngell, Lachy Hulme
description: A shockingly and surprisingly romantic look at five couples as they explore a range of sexual proclivities. Some fetishes are run-of-the-mill, while others are hilariously obscure in this big-hearted comedy about expressing desires.

title: Murder Bury Win
cast: Mikelen Walker, Erich Lane, Henry Alexander Kelly, Craig Cackowski, Brian Slaten, Michael Lovan, Jake Neri, Amy Everson, Melissa Lagosh
description: After a famous game creator drops dead in a suspicious freak accident, three aspiring game designers must turn to their game for guidance. The premise of their game? How to murder someone... and get rid of the body.

title: Lemon
cast: Brett Gelman, Judy Greer, Michael Cera, Nia Long, Shiri Appleby, Fred Melamed, Rhea Perlman, David Paymer, Gillian Jacobs, Martin Starr, Megan Mullally, Jeff Garlin, Marla Gibbs
description: Lemon: a person or thing that proves to be defective, imperfect, or unsatisfactory. Isaac Lachmann is a lemon. His career is going nowhere. His girlfriend of ten years is leaving him. Isaac Lachmann now just watches as his life unravels.

title: Black and White in Color
cast: Jean Carmet, Jacques Dufilho, Catherine Rouvel, Jacques Spiesser, Maurice Barrier
description: French colonists in Africa find themselves at war with their German neighbors. Deciding that they must do their proper duty and fight the Germans, they promptly conscript the local native population. A young, idealistic French geographer seems to be the only rational person in the town, and he takes over control of the war after several bungles on the part of the others.

title: Warrior Queen
cast: Sybil Danning, Donald Pleasence, Rick Hill, Josephine Jacqueline Jones, Tally Chanel, Samantha Fox, Suzanna Smith, David Brandon, Mario Cruciani, Marco Tullio Cau
description: Drama directed by Chuck Vincent, starring Sybil Danning and Donald Pleasence. In ancient Pompeii, the kindhearted Roman emperor's wife works secretly to help slaves escape their harsh lives as non-stop cleaners and sex objects. As the queen gets more and more involved in her quest for equality she puts her own life at risk.

title: The Lair of the White Worm
cast: Hugh Grant, Amanda Donohoe, Catherine Oxenberg
description: After a mysterious skull is unearthed, it's stolen and used by its new owner to worship a pagan god who hungers for the taste of virginal flesh in this cheeky horror-comedy.

title: Six Weeks
cast: Dudley Moore, Mary Tyler Moore, Katherine Healy, Shannon Wilcox, Bill Calvert
description: In this heart-warming drama, a terminally ill young girl strives to bring together her wealthy mother (Mary Tyler Moore) and a California politician (Dudley Moore), fulfilling her dream of having a family during the last six weeks of her life.

title: Harlan County War
cast: Holly Hunter, Stellan Skarsgård, Ted Levine, Wayne Robson, Alex House, Charlotte Arnold, Ker Wells, Jennifer Irwin, Timothy Burd, Rufus Crawford, Cliff Saunders, Deborah Pollitt, Tom Harvey, Regina Dorsea, Helen Hughes
description: A Kentucky woman whose mine-worker husband is nearly killed in a cave-in, and whose father is slowly dying of black lung disease, joins the picket lines for a long, violent strike.

title: Sideways
cast: Paul Giamatti, Sandra Oh, Thomas Haden Church, Virginia Madsen, Marylouise Burke, Jessica Hecht, Missy Doty, M.C. Gainey, Patrick Gallagher, Alex Kalognomos, Joe Marinelli, Alysia Reiner, M. C. Gainey
description: A struggling writer and his has-been actor best friend get into all kinds of trouble when they embark on a wine tasting tour prior to the best friend's wedding.

title: Server Sundaram
cast: Nagesh, R. Muthuraman, K. R. Vijaya, Major Sundarrajan, Manorama
description: Nagesh plays the lead role in the movie. Nagesh lives a contended life of a waiter with his mother. He falls in love with K.R.Vijaya who comes frequently to the hotel he works but K.R.vijaya is not interested. Nagesh ventures into movies with the help of his friend Muthuraman. The rest of the movie is about how he excels in movies and whether he gets his ladylove.

title: Separate Lives
cast: James Belushi, Linda Hamilton, Vera Miles, Elisabeth Moss
description: When a murder detective (James Belushi) is asked by an attractive psychology professor to watch over her, he becomes aware of her split personality. Despite a seemingly dark side to her character, he begins to develop feelings for her, even choosing to ignore signs that point to her as a suspect in a murder case.

title: Ring of Fire II: Blood and Steel
cast: Maria Ford, Vince Murdocco, Don Wilson
description: A martial-arts fighter battles murderous gang members and the henchmen of an evil underground fighting champion to save his girlfriend.

title: Nobel Son
cast: Alan Rickman, Mary Steenburgen, Bill Pullman, Eliza Dushku, Danny DeVito, Bryan Greenberg
description: On the eve of Barkley Michaelson's father receiving the Nobel Prize, Barkley is kidnapped and the requested ransom is the $2,000,000 in Nobel Prize money. When his father refuses to pay it starts a venomous tale of familial dysfunction, lust, betrayal and ultimately revenge.

title: CBGB
cast: Alan Rickman, Malin Akerman, Justin Bartha, Johnny Galecki, Kyle Gallner, Ashley Greene, Rupert Grint, Bradley Whitford, Joel David Moore, Taylor Hawkins
description: Alan Rickman stars as legendary NYC club owner Hilly Kristal, who during the 1970s, wanted to create a venue for country, bluegrass and blues music (thus the name CBGB). When those acts became difficult to book, he shifted the club's focus to local bands playing original music, launching the careers of Patti Smith, Blondie, the Talking Heads and the Ramones and helping to define the punk scene.

title: Machete
cast: Danny Trejo, Steven Seagal, Michelle Rodriguez, Jeff Fahey, Cheech Marin, Lindsay Lohan, Don Johnson, Jessica Alba, Robert De Niro
description: HD. A former Mexican federale unleashes his vengeful fury on both sides of the border in this throwback to '70s exploitation cinema.

title: La Bamba
cast: Lou Diamond Phillips, Esai Morales, Rosana De Soto, Elizabeth Pena, Danielle Von Zerneck, Joe Pantoliano, Rick Dees, Marshall Crenshaw, Brian Setzer, Rosanna Desoto
description: The story of rocker Ritchie Valens - an LA teenager whose rising musical star was hitched to a fateful winter 1959 tour with Buddy Holly. Winning soundtrack by Los Lobos.

title: In Her Shoes
cast: Cameron Diaz, Toni Collette, Shirley MacLaine, Mark Feuerstein
description: HD. Two sisters who have only one thing in common – their shoe size – have a falling out that leads both in surprising new directions.

title: The Bedroom Window
cast: Steve Guttenberg, Elizabeth McGovern, Isabelle Huppert
description: Terry is having an affair with his boss's wife, who witnesses an attempted murder from his apartment. He agrees to report the crime himself to keep their liaison a secret but soon becomes caught in a dangerous web. Directed by Oscar winner Curtis Hanson.

title: The River Wild
cast: Meryl Streep, Kevin Bacon, David Strathairn, Joseph Mazzello, John C. Reilly, Benjamin Bratt, Elizabeth Hoffman, William Lucking, Diane Delano
description: A turbulent vacation turns deadly when a fugitive and his crew kidnap a river rafting guide and her family, forcing them down the dangerous river.

title: Her Desperate Choice
cast: Faith Ford, Kyle Secor, Hanna Hall, Nigel Bennett, Lynne Cormack
description: When her abusive ex-husband wins custody of her daughter, Jody Murdoch realizes the only way to keep her safe is to kidnap her and start a new life on the run. But will mother and dauther ever find safety and happiness as they flee from town to town?

title: Dust
cast: David Wenham, Joseph Fiennes, Anne Brochet, Adrian Lester
description: Two separate stories are intricately woven throughout this unique film of friendship and love.

title: Dear Mr. Gacy
cast: William Forsythe, Jesse Moss, Emma Lahana
description: A chilling true story about the bizarre correspondence between an ambitious criminology student (Jesse Moss) and John Wayne Gacy (William Forsythe), a convicted serial killer.

title: Caught
cast: Anna Camp, Stefanie Scott, Sam Page, Amelia Rose Blaire
description: Inspired by a true story, a desperate housewife kidnaps her husband's teenage mistress as a prank, but her plans soon spiral out of control.

title: Catch Me If You Can
cast: Leonardo DiCaprio, Tom Hanks, Christopher Walken, Martin Sheen, Nathalie Baye, Amy Adams, James Brolin, Brian Howe, Frank John Hughes, Steve Eastin
description: From three-time Oscar winning director Steven Spielberg, Catch Me If You Can follows Frank W. Abagnale, Jr. as he successfully passes himself off as a pilot, a lawyer and a doctor - all before his 21st birthday!

title: Jaws
cast: Roy Scheider, Robert Shaw, Richard Dreyfuss, Lorraine Gary, Murray Hamilton, Carl Gottlieb, Jeffrey Kramer, Susan Backlinie, Jonathan Filley, Ted Grossman
description: When an insatiable great white shark terrorizes Amity Island, a police chief, an oceanographer and a grizzled shark hunter seek to destroy the beast.

title: The BFG
cast: Mark Rylance, Ruby Barnhill, Penelope Wilton, Jemaine Clement, Rebecca Hall, Rafe Spall, Bill Hader, Ólafur Darri Ólafsson, Adam Godley, Michael Adamthwaite, Daniel Bacon, Jonathan Holmes, Chris Gibbs, Paul Moniz de Sa
description: A little orphan meets up with a kind giant who's supposed to eat her but instead protects her from some truly horrible giants who terrorize them both.

title: Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom
cast: Harrison Ford, Kate Capshaw, Amrish Puri, Roshan Seth, Philip Stone, Roy Chiao, Jonathan Ke Quan, David Yip, Ric Young, Chua Kah Joo
description: Indiana Jones, his young sidekick and a spoiled songbird get more than they bargained for when they go to India in search of a missing magical stone.

title: Lincoln
cast: Daniel Day-Lewis, Sally Field, David Strathairn, Joseph Gordon-Levitt, James Spader, Hal Holbrook, Tommy Lee Jones, Jackie Earle Haley, John Hawkes, Jared Harris, Joseph Cross, Tim Blake Nelson, David Oyelowo, Bruce McGill
description: Director Steven Spielberg takes on the towering legacy of Abraham Lincoln, focusing on his stewardship of the Union during the Civil War years.

title: An Imperfect Murder
cast: Sienna Miller, Alec Baldwin, Charles Grodin, Colleen Camp, John Buffalo Mailer, Nick Mathews, Steven Prescod, Oliver "Power" Grant, James Toback
description: Haunted by a nightmare involving her abusive ex-boyfriend, an actress begins to question her reality and whether the incident took place.

title: Tyson
cast: Mike Tyson, Trevor Berbick
description: In this surprisingly emotional documentary, heavyweight champ Mike Tyson analyzes the controversies surrounding his career and turbulent private life.

title: The White Orchid
cast: Olivia Thirlby, John Carroll Lynch, Jennifer Beals
description: A shy Social Services investigator is reluctantly assigned to an unsolved, small-town homicide case. Taking both personal and professional chances, she slowly assumes the identity of the enigmatic blond victim - known only as "The White Orchid" - in hopes of solving the mysterious murder.

title: The Flock
cast: Richard Gere, Claire Danes, KaDee Strickland, Ray Wise
description: This film is about a hyper-vigilant employee of the department of public safety who, while training his young female replacement, has to track down a missing girl who he is convinced is connected to a paroled sex offender he is investigating.

title: Pioneer
cast: Aksel Hennie, Wes Bentley, Stephanie Sigman
description: Set at the beginning of the Norwegian oil boom, authorities aim to bring the 500 meter deep oil ashore. Petter and his brother Knut, have the courage to take on mission, but a tragic accident occurs. Petter realizes that his life is at stake.

title: Copenhagen
cast: Stephen Rea, Daniel Craig, Francesca Annis
description: Based on the acclaimed stage play by Michael Frayn. Long after their deaths, Neils Bohr and Werner Heisenberg look back on their 1941 meeting in occupied Copenhagen. Old friends, Bohr and Heisenberg revolutionized physics in the 1920s but by 1941 were on opposing sides in the Second World War. The meeting was awkward and fraught with danger so why did Heisenberg return?

title: The Whistleblower
cast: Rachel Weisz, Vanessa Redgrave, Monica Bellucci, David Strathairn, Benedict Cumberbatch, Liam Cunningham, Luke Treadaway
description: This ripped-from-the-headlines thriller is inspired by actual events. Kathy Bolkovac (Rachel Weisz), a Nebraskan police officer, takes a job as a peacekeeper in post-war Bosnia. Her expectations of helping to rebuild a devastated country are dashed when she uncovers a dangerous reality of corruption, cover-up and intrigue amid a world of private contractors and multinational diplomatic doubletalk.

title: Lower Learning
cast: Rob Corddry, Jason Biggs, Eva Longoria Parker
description: Welcome to Geraldine Ferraro Elementary, where the teachers are drunk, lazy, or psychotic, every child has been left behind, and burned-out Vice Principal Tom Willoman (Jason Biggs) is barely holding on.

title: Delicatessen
cast: Dominique Pinon, Marie-Laure Dougnac, Jean-Claude Dreyfus, Karin Viard, Rufus, Ticky Holgado, Jean-Francois Perrier
description: Post-apocalyptic surrealist black comedy about the landlord of an apartment building who occasionally prepares a delicacy for his odd tenants.

title: Bit
cast: Diana Hopper, Nicole Maines, James Paxton
description: Laurel moves to LA and falls in with a gang of vampires. Not knowing if they want to kill her, befriend her or turn her, she learns to understand the love and dangers of her new and first group of friends.

title: Wrong Place, Wrong Time
cast: Franziska Schissler, Justin Price, Bianca Stein, Alex Ryan Brown
description: An elite team of vigilantes plot to steal 14 billion dollars of laundered money from a notorious mob boss. After being double-crossed, they find refuge in the middle of nowhere with a mysterious family carrying an unsettling secret.

title: Kansas City
cast: Jennifer Jason Leigh, Steve Buscemi, Miranda Richardson
description: Blondie O'Hara resorts to desperate measures when her low-level hood husband Johnny gets caught trying to steal from Seldom Seen, a local crime boss operating out of jazz haunt The Hey-Hey Club. Out on a limb, Blondie kidnaps laudanum-addled socialite Carolyn, hoping her influential politician husband can pull the right strings and get Johnny out of Seldom Seen's clutches.

title: Popeye
cast: Robin Williams, Shelley Duvall, Ray Walston, Paul Dooley, Paul L. Smith, Richard Libertini, Donald Moffat, Macintyre Dixon, Roberta Maxwell, Donovan Scott
description: During a storm that wrecks his ship, super-strong sailor Popeye washes ashore and winds up rooming at the Oyl household, where he meets Olive.

title: Black Butterfly
cast: Antonio Banderas, Jonathan Rhys Meyers, Piper Perabo
description: Antonio Banderas, Jonathan Rhys Meyers, and Piper Perabo headline this chilling tale of a writer who takes in a mysterious drifter at his remote cabin and soon finds himself in a dangerous situation spiraling out of control.

title: The Scoundrels
cast: Wu Kang-ren, JC Lin, Nana Lee
description: A disgraced basketball star working for a local gangster plunges deeper into a cruel criminal underworld when he gets involved with the city's most notorious thief.

title: Hell on Wheels
cast: Marty Robbins, John Ashley, Gigi Perreau, Robert Dornan
description: A pair of brothers-one is an awesome race car driver who's popular with the ladies, and the other is a smart mechanic-team up to compete against some stock car racing's best, but are torn apart when one falls in love with the other's girlfriend.

title: Breakable You
cast: Holly Hunter, Tony Shalhoub, Alfred Molina, Cristin Milioti
description: The film follows the Wellers, A dynamic New York City family as they come to terms with themselves and each other.

title: Beauty and the Beast
cast: Estella Warren, Damien Garvey, Rhett Giles, Melissa Thompson, Victor Parascos
description: A dark twist on the morality tale of forbidden love between beautiful Belle and the feared forest Beast. As villagers are being brutally murdered and the Beast is hunted down as the one responsible for the mayhem, Belle and Beast team up to defeat the real killer: the power-hungry witch's malevolent troll.

title: 5 Souls
cast: Ian Bohen, Samaire Armstrong, Steve Bacic, Lynn Blackburn
description: How far would you go to save your soul? Noah is haunted by this very question when a shadowy stranger offers him a disturbing choice: kill or be killed.

title: Stalled
cast: Dan Palmer, Tamaryn Payne, Antonia Bernath, Mark Holden
description: A janitor gets trapped in a women's restroom and soon encounters an all-out attack by a hoard of zombies. Blood spews and body parts are flying in this hilarious, yet shocking zombie-fest that will make you checking under the stalls before your next bathroom break!

title: Oh My Kadavule
cast: Ashok Selvan, Ritika Singh, Vani Bhojan, Sha Ra, M. S. Bhaskar
description: Two childhood friends, Anu and Arjun, decide to get married. However, their marital life becomes complicated due to misunderstandings and miscommunication which leads to a divorce.

title: Defendor
cast: Woody Harrelson, Elias Koteas, Michael Kelly, Sandra Oh, Kat Dennings
description: Despite lacking any actual superpowers, Arthur Poppington transforms himself into the costumed vigilante Defendor. But danger beckons when our hero tries to protect a young prostitute from an assailant who turns out to be a corrupt undercover cop.

title: These Old Broads
cast: Carrie Fisher, Shirley MacLaine, Elizabeth Taylor, Nestor Carbonell
description: A 40 year old movie's re-release is a hit and there's focus on the 3 main actresses. The adopted son of one has to make these old broads attend a show together. One problem: they hate each other.

title: Mardi Gras: Spring Break
cast: Josh Gad, Arielle Kebbel, Danneel Harris, Regina Hall, Nicholas D'Agosto, Bret Harrison, Carmen Electra
description: 3 best friends travel to Mardis Gras during their senior year of college with the hopes of getting some action.

title: Guigo Offline
cast: Antonio Haddad Aguerre, Pedro Goifman, Alexandre Cioletti, Roberto Rezende
description: Guigo is the son of separated parents and one day, he and his friend Túlio travel with his father, Roberto, and his friend, Paulo. The trip would have everything to go well, if there was internet signal. The lack of communication makes Guigo anxious. Besides, he will have yet to deal with another situation: Paulo is, in fact, his father's boyfriend.

title: Funny Face
cast: Cosmo Jarvis, Dela Meskienyar, Jonny Lee Miller, Victor Garber, Jeremy Bobb, Dan Hedaya, Rhea Perlman
description: The destruction of his grandparents' home leads a young man to take revenge under a masked persona

title: Deceit
cast: Emmanuelle Chriqui, Matt Long, Luke Mably
description: A young man returns to hometown after his father's death and finds his two best married friends. His decision to stay rekindles the old attraction to his friend's wife, and the woman is caught in between the two men.

title: Conspiracy
cast: Val Kilmer, Jennifer Esposito, Gary Cole
description: A seasoned senior enlisted special operations United States Marine is wounded during combat operations in Iraq. He retires from the Marine Corps and visits a friend in the south west. There he discovers his friend has disappeared and no one will even admit to knowing of him.

title: Ghost Town
cast: Herbert Coward, Bill McKinney, DJ Perry
description: Lonesome Dove meets 3:10 to Yuma in this bullet ridden tale of revenge, redemption and courage

title: Cruel Intentions 2
cast: Amy Adams, Mimi Rogers
description: This takes place several years before Cruel Intentions, back to when Kathryn first meets Sebastian, their sexual attraction to each other and their enjoyment in destroying the lives of their peers.

title: Falling Inn Love
cast: Christina Milian, Adam Demos, Jeffrey Bowyer-Chapman, Anna Jullienne, Claire Chitham, Blair Strang, Jonathan Martin, William Walker, Daniel Watterson, Simone Walker
description: When a San Francisco exec wins a New Zealand inn, she ditches city life to remodel and flip the rustic property with help from a handsome contractor.

title: College Road Trip
cast: Martin Lawrence, Raven-Symoné , Donny Osmond, Brenda Song, Will Sasso, Eshaya Draper
description: An overprotective dad joins his daughter in search of the perfect college.

title: The Good Night
cast: Danny DeVito, Martin Freeman, Gwyneth Paltrow, Penelope Cruz, Keith Allen, Steffan Boje, Sonia Doubell, Michael Gambon, Stephen Graham, Kate Harper, Gael Le Cornec, Bruno Lastra, Martino Lazzeri, Meredith MacNeill, Simon Pegg, Amber Sealey, Deva Bennett Skye, Joyce Springer, Finty Williams, Juliana Kiehl
description: Penélope Cruz, Martin Freeman, Gwyneth Paltrow, and Danny DeVito co-star in this dark comedy about an obsessed man who will do anything to make his passion-filled dream life a reality.

title: Out of Bounds
cast: Anthony Michael Hall, Jenny Wright, Jeff Kober, Glynn Turman, Raymond J. Barry, Meat Loaf, Jerry Levine, Pepe Serna, John Vickery
description: Daryl's parents ship him off to the big city to live with his brother, hoping he will have a better life there. After a baggage mix-up at the airport, Daryl finds himself in possession of a drug cache, which a drug dealer wants back.

title: Montana
cast: Philip Seymour Hoffman, Kyra Sedgwick, Stanley Tucci, Robin Tunney, Robbie Coltrane, John Ritter, Ethan Embry
description: A hit woman and her sickly boyfriend try to find out who's plotting to kill her boss.

title: Max and Me
cast: Matthew Erick White, Lily Bleu Andrew, Mathew Odette, Grant Anstine, Melissa Ponzio
description: A coming of age story about an awkward teenage boy who falls in love with the girl next door, who he soon discovers passed away the year before from Cystic Fibrosis, and he's in love with a ghost.

title: Madhoshi
cast: John Abraham, Bipasha Basu, Priyanshu Chatterjee, Dolly Bindra, Anang Desai, Smita Jaykar, Dinesh Kaushik, Shweta Tiwari
description: Despite being engaged to Arpit, Anupama falls in love with Aman, a stranger. However, when her family members decide to meet him, they are shocked to discover that a person named Aman does not exist.

title: Singh Saab the Great
cast: Sunny Deol, Urvashi Rautela, Prakash Raj, Amrita Rao, Anjali Abrol, Johnny Lever, Sanjay Mishra, Yashpal Sharma, Manoj Pahwa, Raj Premi
description: As the result of a TV journalist's curiosity, the amazing saga of an honorable government tax collector's past comes to light.

title: Lake Michigan Monster
cast: Ryland Brickson Cole Tews, Erick West, Beulah Peters, Daniel Long
description: On the shores of Lake Michigan, Captain Seafield enlists a crew of misfits in a bid to slay the hellish monster that prowls the depths. But as his obsession with exacting revenge on the creature that killed his father threatens to consume him, can weapons expert Sean Shaughnessy, sonar whiz Nedge Pepsi and N.A.V.Y. (Nautical Athletes and adVenture Yunit) officer Dick Flynn hold the show together?

title: Dhilluku Dhuddu 2
cast: Santhanam, Shritha Sivadas, Deepti, Rajendran, Bipin, Urvashi
description: In a bid to escape from Viji's antics, his neighbours lure him to fall in love with Maya. However, everything turns upside down when he realises that a ghost is protecting Maya.

title: Crooked Arrows
cast: Brandon Routh, Gil Birmingham, Crystal Allen
description: A story centered on a Native American lacrosse team making its way through a prep school league tournament.

title: Road Trip: Beer Pong
cast: Nestor Aaron Absera, Julianna Guill, Preston Jones, Julia Levy-Boeken, Danny Pudi, Michael Trotter, Daniel Newman, DJ Qualls
description: When three college pals hit the road to compete in a big-time beer pong tournament, their trip morphs into an outrageous odyssey.

title: Zenon: Z3
cast: Kirsten Storms, Lauren Maltby, Alyson Morgan, Stuart Pankin, Holly Fulger, Ben Easter
description: It's up to Zenon and her friends when moon goddess Selena threatens Earth.

title: Silukkuvarupatti Singam
cast: Vishnu Vishal, Regina Cassandra, P. Ravi Shankar, Anandaraj, Yogi Babu, Karunakaran
description: Sathyamoorthy, a carefree police officer who is not enthusiastic about his job, is forced to change his attitude after he accidentally arrests a man from a pub, who happens to be a gangster.

title: Once Upon a Time in China IV
cast: Wenzhuo Zhao, Jean Wang, Siu Chung Mok, Xin Xin Xiong, Billy Chow
description: Wong Fei Hung must deal with both foreign threats and the nationalist Red Lantern Society in this continuation of the popular kung fu series.

title: Lovesick
cast: Jacob Tierney, Jessica Pare, Jay Baruchel, Ali Tataryn, Fred Penner, Sarah Constible
description: Dash is 33, broke, depressed and still in love with his ex, Lauren, who suddenly gets engaged. It all seems hopeless until he meets Nora - a spontaneous and unforgettable woman. But timing is everything, and Nora's not going to wait around.

title: Lost Horizon
cast: Peter Finch, Liv Ullmann, Sally Kellerman, George Kennedy, Michael York, Olivia Hussey, Bobby Van, James Shigeta, John Gielgud
description: While escaping war-torn China, a group of Europeans crash in the Himalayas, where they are rescued and taken to the mysterious Valley of the Blue Moon, Shangri-La.

title: Lake Placid: The Final Chapter
cast: Robert Englund, Elisabeth Rohm, Yancy Butler, Poppy Lee Friar, Daniel Black, Jonas Talkington, Paul Nicholls, Caroline Ford, Dan Black, Jeff Stewart, Sewell Whitney, Elena Boeva, Benedict Smith, Scarlett Byrne, Ako Mitchell, Peter Ladjev, Kitodar Todorov, Marina Gerganova, Terry Randall, Zara Dimitrova, Borisa Tutundjieva
description: A rogue game warden breaks out her guns after the schemes of an obsessed poacher lands a group of high school students into the midst of the man-eating crocodile "nature preserve."

title: Sniper: Legacy
cast: Tom Berenger, Chad Michael Collins, Doug Allen, Dominic Mafham, Mercedes Mason, Mark Lewis Jones, Nestor Serrano, Dennis Haysbert, Alex Roe, Yana Marinova
description: When a troubled sniper begins killing officers he blames for a bungled mission, elite marksman Brandon Beckett sets out to neutralize the threat.

title: Tremors: Shrieker Island
cast: Michael Gross, Jon Heder, Caroline Langrishe, Cassie Clare, Matthew Douglas, Sahajak Boonthanakit, David Asavanond, Jackie Cruz, Richard Brake
description: When massive mutant creatures infiltrate an island nature preserve, scientists recruit a legendary monster hunter to battle the beasts.

title: Bulletproof 2
cast: Faizon Love, Kirk Fox, Tony Todd, Pearl Thusi, Cassie Clare, Fiona Ramsey, Neels Clasen, Roxy Nel
description: A special agent abruptly reunites with a criminal – once a former friend – when he attempts to use his identity to infiltrate and take down a cartel.

title: Jarhead: Law of Return
cast: Amaury Nolasco, Devon Sawa, Robert Patrick, Jeff Pierre, Ben Cross, Amos Tamam, Yael Eitan, Tsahi Halevi
description: When a U.S. senator’s son is held captive by Hezbollah militiamen, a group of highly trained soldiers ventures into enemy territory to bring him home.

title: A Chinese Ghost Story
cast: Leslie Cheung, Joey Wang, Wu Ma, Wai Lam, Siu-Ming Lau
description: After a string of bad luck, a debt collector has no other choice than to spend the night in a haunted temple, where he encounters a ravishing female ghost and later battles to save her soul from the control of a wicked tree demon.

title: The Last Time
cast: Michael Keaton, Brendan Fraser, Amber Valetta, Daniel Stern
description: A salesman rediscovers a lust for life after falling for the fiancée of his new business partner, a Midwest transplant finding his footing in New York City.

title: Painkiller
cast: Michael Pare, Bill Oberst Jr., Tom Parnell, Kristina Beringer, Khalimah Gaston, Scot Scurlock
description: In the midst of America's deadly opioid epidemic, an unlikely anti-hero emerges. After losing his daughter to a drug overdose, a broken father begins a vigilante campaign targeting doctors and pharmaceutical executives. Teaming up with a rogue cop, they set out to dismantle this network of white-collar criminals that continue to take lives and devastate families.

title: For Pete's Sake
cast: Barbra Streisand, Michael Sarrazin, Estelle Parsons, Anne Ramsey, Vincent Schiavelli
description: A housewife tries to finance her cab-driving husband's education.

title: Fair Play
cast: Judit Bardos, Anna Geislerová, Eva Josefíková, Ondřej Novák, Roman Zach, Igor Bareš, Jiří Wohanka, Ondřej Malý, Taťjana Medvecká
description: Czechoslovakia in the 1980, young and talented sprinter Anna is selected for the national team and starts training for the Olympics. The team starts a secret medical programme which includes anabolic steroids. Her performance improves, but, after a collapse, she decides to quit using doping, even though her mother is worried that she might not achieve their only chance to escape the Iron Curtain.

title: Eternal Beauty
cast: Sally Hawkins, David Thewlis, Billie Piper, Penelope Wilton, Morfydd Clark, Robert Pugh, Alice Lowe, Robert Aramayo
description: When Jane (Sally Hawkins) is dumped at the altar she has a breakdown and spirals into a chaotic world, where love (both real and imagined) and family relationships collide with both touching and humorous consequences.

title: Young Frankenstein
cast: Marty Feldman, Danny Goldman, Liam Dunn, Cloris Leachman, Teri Garr, Gene Hackman, Peter Boyle, Kenneth Mars, Leon Askin, Arthur Malet, Richard Roth, Lou Cutell, Madeline Kahn, Oscar Beregi, Gene Wilder, Richard Haydn
description: Director Mel Brooks' comic spoof of the Frankenstein (that's 'Fronk-en-steen') films is a comedy classic! Featuring Teri Garr, Madeline Kahn, Cloris Leachman, Gene Hackman and Peter Boyle as The Monster.

title: The Privileged
cast: Sam Trammell, Joshua Close, Laura Harris, Lina Roessler
description: Richard, a promising young lawyer at a prestigious firm, has the perfect future mapped out. However, a costly mistake with a client has put it all at risk. In a desperate attempt to save his job, Richard and his wife spend the weekend at the cottage of a senior partner. The couple is quickly seduced by their hosts' lavish lifestyle but it is clear that something ominous lies below the surface.

title: The Legend of Bagger Vance
cast: Will Smith, Matt Damon, Charlize Theron, Bruce McGill, Joel Gretsch
description: A disillusioned war veteran, Capt. Rannulph Junah (Matt Damon), reluctantly agrees to play a game of golf. He finds the game futile until his caddy, Bagger Vance (Will Smith), teaches him the secret of the authentic golf stroke which turns out also to be the secret to mastering any challenge and finding meaning in life.

title: The Last Face
cast: Charlize Theron, Javier Bardem, Jared Harris, Adele Exarchopoulos
description: Oscar winners Charlize Theron and Javier Bardem are international aid workers in Africa fighting for humanity during civil unrest in this moving drama from two-time Academy Award winner Sean Penn.

title: Silver City
cast: Chris Cooper, Richard Dreyfuss, Danny Huston, Tim Roth, Thora Birch
description: The discovery of a corpse threatens to unravel a bumbling local politician's campaign for governor of Colorado.

title: Oru Adaar Love
cast: Priya Prakash Varrier, Roshan Abdul Rahoof, Noorin Shereef, Siyadh Shajahan
description: With some help from his friends, a teenager begins dating his classmate. However, an incident causes a rift between them and he falls in love with his best friend.

title: No Way Jose
cast: Gillian Jacobs, Adam Goldberg, Emily Osment, Brendan Hines, Ahna O'Reilly, Pat Healy, Anna Belknap, Eric Siegel
description: Jose Stern, an erstwhile indie-rocker relegated to playing children's birthday parties, is on the verge of turning 40 and at a crossroads in his life.

title: Lies in Plain Sight
cast: Martha Higareda, Chad Michael Murray, Yul Vazquez, Benito Martinez, Daniela Bobadilla, Lupe Ontiveros, Kendra Jain, Cheyenne Haynes, Christoph Sanders, Rosie Perez
description: Blind college student Sofia returns home after hearing the news of her cousin Ava's suicide and learns of some hidden, dark secrets the family has been keeping.

title: I Am Durán
cast: Roberto Durán, Robert De Niro, Sylvester Stallone, Robin Durán, Ricky Hatton, Ken Buchanon, Mauricio Sulaiman, Mike Tyson, Oscar de la Hoya, Sugar Ray Leonard
description: Roberto Durán is a boxing behemoth, a titanic figure straddling five epic decades as a fighter ranked as one of the most entertaining, controversial and finest of all time.

title: Hey Jude
cast: Nivin Pauly, Trisha Krishnan, Siddique, Neena Kurup
description: Two odd ball characters, a youngster named Jude and the other, a talented singer named Crystal. When these two characters come together, their lives undergo several changes, leading to love, self-discovery, healing and transformation.

title: Eddie Izzard: Definite Article
cast: Eddie Izzard
description: This superb DVD was recorded at the Shaftesbury Theatre, London, when Eddie was in the middle of her sell-out 12 week run.

title: Eddie Izzard: Unrepeatable
cast: Eddie Izzard
description: Unrepeatable was recorded one night at the Albery Theatre in March 1994, when Eddie Izzard was playing a limited seven week sold-out run of his celebrated stand-up show. A completely new show from her previous thirteen week run at the Ambassadors Theatre the year before, she played to 34,000 people and received more rave reviews than last time.

title: Days of the Bagnold Summer
cast: Monica Dolan, Earl Cave, Elliot Speller-Gillott
description: A teenager spends his summer listening to heavy metal music and trying to get along with his librarian mom.

title: Annie: A Royal Adventure
cast: Joan Collins, Ashley Johnson, George Hearn, Ian McDiarmid, Emily Ann Lloyd
description: The durable little orphan from the funny papers makes her TV movie debut in this M.O.W. Daddy Warbucks is called to London to be knighted, so he takes Annie and her pal Hannah with him, along with Dr. Eli Eon and faithful companions the Asp and Punjab. Little Molly from the orphanage is the girl's stowaway.

title: A Chinese Ghost Story III
cast: Tony Chiu-Wai Leung, Joey Wang, Jacky Cheung, Nina Li Chi, Shun Lau
description: Basically a retread of the first movie, in which the evil Tree Spirit is back with yet another ghost played by Joey Wong. The Swordsman Yen and Leslie Cheung characters are replaced by a Buddhist Abbot and disciple (Tony Leung). Jacky Cheung also pops up again, this time as a money-grabbing swordsman with a neat bag of tricks.

title: True Blue
cast: Tom Berenger, Lori Heuring, Pamela Gidley
description: This dark and gritty thriller has Tom Berenger as a rogue police lieutenant who falls in love with a mysterious woman who leads him into a seedy world where nothing is as it seems.

title: The Turn of the Screw
cast: Michelle Dockery, Sue Johnston, Dan Stevens, Mark Umbers, Nicola Walker, Josef Lindsay, Eva Sayer
description: A hauntingly atmospheric and star-studded adaptation of Henry James' classic gothic horror story. A young, inexperienced governess is hired to look after two small children abandoned by their uncle, following the death of their parents. Unsettled by glimpses of ghostly figures that only she can see, she quickly believes that something malevolent is stalking the children in her care.

title: Ice Princess
cast: Joan Cusack, Kim Cattrall, Michelle Trachtenberg, Hayden Panettiere, Trevor Blumas, Connie Ray
description: A brainy ugly duckling realizes her dream of becoming a champion figure skater.

title: The King of Marvin Gardens
cast: Jack Nicholson, Bruce Dern, Ellen Burstyn, Julia Anne Robinson, Benjamin "Scatman" Crothers, Charles LaVine
description: In a film that captures all the sadness of an American dream gone wrong, Bruce Dern concocts impossible get-rich-quick schemes and insists on trying them out on his brother and girlfriend. Dern's final scheme, to build a Hawaiian resort with embezzled money from his mobster boss, ends in tragedy for all involved.

title: The Alamo
cast: Dennis Quaid, Billy Bob Thornton, Patrick Wilson, Jason Patric
description: In 1836, Texans hold the Alamo for 13 days while under siege.

title: Surrender, Dorothy
cast: Diane Keaton, Tom Everett Scott, Alexa Davalos, Lauren German, Josh Hopkins, Chris Pine, Peter Riegert, Leonard Stone, Race Owen
description: When her daughter Sara (Davalos) unexpectedly passes away, Natalie (Keaton) retreats to the summer home where she and Sara used to visit. Time with her best friends and some of Sara's friends help her deal with her loss.

title: Scenes of a Sexual Nature
cast: Tom Hardy, Ewan McGregor, Mark Strong, Andrew Lincoln, Hugh Bonneville, Gina McKee, Catherine Tate, Douglas Hodge, Polly Walker
description: This British comedy stars an incredible home-grown cast including Tom Hardy (Mad Max: Fury Road), Ewan McGregor, (Trainspotting), Catherine Tate (Doctor Who), Mark Strong (1917), Hugh Bonneville (Notting Hill), Andrew Lincoln (Love Actually) and Adrian Lester (The Day After Tomorrow). On the lush green lawns of London's Hampstead Heath, a variety of couples sort through their romantic dilemmas.

title: Scare Campaign
cast: Meegan Warner, Ian Meadows, Olivia DeJonge, Josh Quong Tart
description: The crew of a reality TV prank show facing dwindling ratings decides to up the ante by setting up a terrifying prank in an abandoned asylum. Things go horribly wrong when they prank the wrong guy. Brothers Colin and Cameron Cairnes (100 Bloody Acres) deliver a night of blood soaked terror full of twists and turns that will satisfy any gore hound.

title: Roger Dodger
cast: Jennifer Beals, Elizabeth Berkley, Jesse, Eisenberg, Isabella Rossellini, Campbell Scott
description: Roger guides his 16 year-old nephew through New York City's wild nightlift for an all-night crash course in the art of seduction.

title: Retreat
cast: Thandiwe Newton, Cillian Murphy, Jamie Bell, Jimmy Yuill, Marilyn Mantle
description: Kate and Martin escape from personal tragedy to an Island Retreat. Cut off from the outside world, their attempts to recover are shattered when a Man is washed ashore, with news of airborne killer disease that is sweeping through Europe.

title: Redcon-1
cast: Oris Erhuero,  Carlos Gallardo, Mark Strange
description: After a deadly viral outbreak, an elite squad of special force soldiers must infiltrate a quarantine zone to rescue a scientist who holds the only cure to save mankind. In a last attempt to contain the mutated virus, they launch a final strike against the infected, risking all of humanity in the process.

title: Nightlight
cast: Shelby Young, Chloe Bridges, Carter Jenkins, Mitch Hewer, Taylor Ashley Murphy
description: A night of flashlight games and ghost stories becomes a journey into absolute terror when five teens awaken a demonic presence in the woods.

title: Mutants
cast: Michael Ironside, Louis Herthum, Tony Senzamici
description: A mad scientist inadvertently unleashes the apocalypse while attempting to create an additive for a greedy manufacturer.

title: Carnivorous
cast: DMX, Wes Brown, Louis Herthum
description: In the countryside, Alan and his friend Becky steal a creepy wooden box with a powerful voodoo stick inside from his voodooistic neighbor.

title: Light Sleeper
cast: Willem Dafoe, Susan Sarandon, Dana Delany, David Clennon, Mary Beth Hurt
description: John Letour (Dafoe) is a good man in a bad business, working for Ann (Sarandon) on the wrong side of the law, and he wants out. Will he get out before it's too late?

title: Insanitarium
cast: Jesse Metcalfe, Kiele Sanchez, Kevin Sussman, Peter Stormare, Olivia Munn, Carla Gallo
description: Jesse Metcalfe (Desperate Housewives) stars in this thriller about a man who cons himself to a mental hospital to break out his sister. Once inside, he learns that a doctor (Peter Stormare, Fargo) is mercilessly using his patients as lab rats and turning them into bloodthirsty killers. Trapped inside an inescapable labyrinth, will they find a way out before the relentless cannibals hunt them down?

title: I Still Know What You Did Last Summer
cast: Jennifer Hewitt, Freddie Prinze Jr., Brandy, Mekhi Phifer, Matthew Settle, Jennifer Esposito
description: The horror of last summer stalks Julie James and her friends in the Bahamas!

title: Glass House: The Good Mother
cast: Angie Harmon, Joel Gretsch, Jordan Hinson, Bobby Coleman, Jason London
description: After losing their parents in a tragic accident, teenager Abby Snow and her younger brother Ethan find a new home with Eve (Angie Harmon) and Raymond Goode (Joel Gretsch). While moving into their adoptive parents' remote mansion, the siblings come to the shocking realization that the Goodes are not as they seem, and the Snows' dreams of love and security become a nightmare of cruelty and terror.

title: Extracurricular
cast: Keenan Tracey, Brittany Raymond, Spencer Macpherson, Brittany Teo, Luke Goss
description: Four overachieving high school friends have a secret pastime: planning and executing murders. But when one of their plans goes shockingly awry, the relationship between the group is put to the test.

title: Excision
cast: Annalynne McCord, Traci Lords, Roger Bart, Malcolm McDowell, Ariel Winter, Jeremy Sumpter

Turns out that Carlos is not alone in s..

title: All About My Mother
cast: Marisa Peredes, Penelope Cruz, Candela Pena, Cecilia Roth, Rosa Maria Sarda, Antonia San Juan
description: Pedro Almodovar's Oscar(r)-winning comedy (Best Foreign Film, 1999) about a bereaved mother, an overwrought actress, her jealous lover and a pregnant nun.

title: The Tribe
cast: Jeremy Northam, Joely Richardson, Anna Friel, Jonathan Rhys Myers
description: Jamie is an ambitious employee at a visionary property company which has purchased an unusual building on the edge of the city. It is occupied by a mysterious group of young people, so Jamie is sent in to evict them. They appear to be a cult, led by the seductive Emily. Jamie is attracted to Emily, and the younger, fearless, Lizzie and is overwhelmed by their magical and erotic lifestyle.

title: Strumpet
cast: Christopher Eccleston, Jenna G.
description: Strayman, a spontaneous poet, is landlord to a pack of stray dogs. Unable to resist another of life's strays, he hooks up with Strumpet, a shy, homeless girl with a gift for music. After Strayman's neighbor overhears them singing, the three set off for London in search of fame, fortune and Top of the Pops. This compulsive, experimental film is heartwarming, moving and visually startling.

title: Trainspotting
cast: Ewan McGregor, Ewen Bremner, Jonny Lee Miller, Kevin McKidd, Robert Carlyle, Kelly Macdonald, Peter Mullan, James Cosmo, Eileen Nicholas, Susan Vidler, Pauline Lynch, Shirley Henderson

title: Spider's Web
cast: Stephen Baldwin, Kari Wuhrer, Benjamin King, Scott Williamson, Michael Gregory, George Lazenby, George Murdock, Monique Alexander, Matt Borlenghi, Lavelle Roby
description: A wily businessman plots with a sultry executive to swindle $40 million from his father. But who is conning who?

title: Irish Jam
cast: Dudley Sutton, Eddie Griffith, Anna Friel
description: Upon discovering that their town is up for sale, crafty Irish villagers scheme to raise the money to prevent the buy-out. They hold a poetry contest with a tempting grand prize – the deed to their local pub. But what could happen when a duplicitous American rapper emerges as the best poet around?

title: Everybody's Talking About Jamie
cast: Max Harwood, Sarah Lancashire, Lauren Patel, Shobna Gulati, Ralph Ineson, Adeel Akhtar, Sharon Horgan, Richard E. Grant
description: Despite obstacles, 16-year-old Jamie has the courage to fabulously follow his unconventional dream in this inspiring true story turned musical sensation.

title: Alabama's Ghost
cast: Christopher Brooks
description: A nightclub stage manager stumbles upon a forgotten, secret chamber underneath his nightclub. Inside is an old magician's belongings. He tries on the costume and he becomes "Alabama, King of the Cosmos." This new identity leads to a lot more than he bargained for. This wild film features voodoo, ghosts, vampires, robots, magicians, hippies, rock concerts, and more.

title: Supercon
cast: Ryan Kwanten, Maggie Grace, Mike Epps, Brooks Braselman, Russell Peters, Clancy Brown, John Malkovich
description: A group of comic convention performers come together over the 4th of July weekend to take down a shady promoter and ego mania star.

title: Raven
cast: Jeffrey Meek, Lee Majors
description: A secret agent leads a group of government mercenaries seeking a secret decoder worth $50 million.

title: Cheer Up
cast: Ashton McGraw, TiaRamy Maloy, Tyler Maddox
description: A group of young women who are considered social misfits get together to join the schools Cheer team.

title: Bell Bottom
cast: Akshay Kumar, Vaani Kapoor, Lara Dutta, Huma Qureshi, Adil Hussain, Denzil Smith, Dolly Ahluwalia
description: By the early ‘80s India had already witnessed multiple airplane hijacks. In 1984, the country was made to face another such challenge. BellBottom, a RAW Agent played by Akshay Kumar, sees through the plan and thus begins India's first overseas covert operation. An operation, lead by a forgotten hero, that went on to create one of the most defining moments for India.

title: Paranoia
cast: Harrison Ford, Liam Hemsworth, Amber Heard, Gary Oldman, Lucas Till
description: An entry-level employee at a powerful corporation finds himself occupying a corner office, but at a dangerous price: he must spy on his boss's old mentor to secure for him a multi-billion dollar advantage.

title: Legally Blonde
cast: Reese Witherspoon, Luke Wilson, Selma Blair, Matthew Davis, Victor Garber, Jennifer Coolidge
description: When dazzling L.A. sorority girl Elle Woods gets dumped by her snobby boyfriend, she decides to win him back by following him to Harvard Law School.

title: Scorned
cast: Billy Zane,  AnnaLynne McCord,  Viva Bianca
description: A romantic weekend turns horrific when Sadie discovers her boyfriend Kevin is having an affair with her best friend Jennifer.

title: Evan Almighty
cast: Steve Carell, Morgan Freeman, Lauren Graham, Johnny Simmons, Graham Phillips, Jimmy Bennett, John Goodman, Wanda Sykes, John Michael Higgins, Jonah Hill, Molly Shannon, Harve Presnell, P.J. Byrne, Ralph Louis Harris, Arden Myrin, Brian Howe, Ralph P. Martin, Maile Flanagan, Angela Martinez, Ed Helms, David Barrera, Jeremiah Birkett, Jesse Burch, Rachael Harris, Casey Strand, Wayne Wilderson, Dean Norris, Scott Rollins, Madison Mason, Bruce Gray, Paul Collins, Lisa Kushell, Judith Benezra, Krista Carpenter, Gerald Downey, Simon Helberg, Dylan Jones, Jay Lay, Suzy Nakamura, Matt Price, Irene Rosen, Larry Sullivan, Audrey Wasilewski, Jon Wellner, Channing Chase, Jim Doughan, Shelley Dowdy, Meagen Fay, Pete Gardner, Gregg Goulet, Jan Hoag, Harry S. Murphy, Ruth Williamson, Don Dowe, Shashawnee Hall, Lucia Forte, Deborah Carson, Lamont Thompson, Larry Dorf, Tom Beyer, Topper Shutt, Juan M. Fern?ndez, Bridget White, Roxana Ortega, Brendan Patrick Connor, Charlie Hartsock, William Dennis Hunt, Franklin Dennis Jones, Lillian Lehman, Catherine McGoohan, Phil Reeves, Edmund L. Shaff, Tucke
description: Everyone's favorite funnyman Steve Carell is at his hilarious best as junior congressman Evan Baxter, whose wish to "change the world" is heard by none other than God. When God appears with the perplexing request to build an ark, Evan is sure he is losing it.

title: The Nutty Professor
cast: Eddie Murphy, Jada Pinkett Smith, James Coburn, Larry Miller, Dave Chappelle, John Ales, Patricia Wilson, Jamal Mixon
description: After being made fun of for his weight, a kind and brainy professor takes a dose of a revolutionary formula that changes more than just his appearance.

description: A wealthy family's home is invaded during a game of hide-and-seek by a pack cultists. Josie, the babysitter hides in plain sight prepared and armed with a handful of survival skills. She battles the cult and her fears through a long night of terror. Ultimately good defeats evil and she triumphs, but not before a cruel twist reveals the cult were just foot soldiers for a much greater evil.

title: I'll Follow You Down
cast: Haley Joel Osment, Gillian Anderson, Rufus Sewell, Victor Garber
description: After the disappearance of an accomplished physicist (Rufus Sewell), his son Erol (Haley Joel Osment) and wife Marika (Gillian Anderson) struggle to cope. Years later, now a young scientist himself, Erol discovers a formula that could kill him, throw him into the unknown...or bring his family back together.

description: A newly rich New Jersey trucker moves to Hollywood and creates a slew of hit TV shows by manipulating the ratings system with help from his girlfriend in the ratings business.

title: Sunny
cast: Jayasurya
description: The life of a failed musician, sunny takes a dramatic turn as he smuggles himself back from Dubai to Kerala in midst of a global pandemic and shuts himself from the society.

title: Russian Raid
cast: Ivan Kotik, Igor Stardseltsev
description: An ex soldier returns to Russia as a mercenary seeking to avenge his fathers death after he was brutally murder in a secret missile factory.

title: Molly and Me
cast: Gracie Fields, Roddy McDowall, Monty Woolley, Reginal Gardiner, Natalie Schafer
description: Molly (Fields), a poor struggling actress, decides to "play the part" of housekeeper for wealthy former politician John Graham (Wooley). However, Mr. Graham is hard to get along with, to the point that he has chased his wife and other servants away, and alienated his son Jimmy (McDowall). Graham's only ally is butler Peabody (Gardiner), whom she later finds out is also a former actor. Molly won't take Graham's nonsense, and teaches him about how to treat other people, and reconcile with his son. And as the other servants quit, Molly steadily replaces them with her old theater friends, so that the house soon becomes a former actor refuge! A wonderful screwball comedy, and Gracie Field's last movie appearance.

title: Creating Freedom: The Lottery of Birth
cast: Michael Albert, Stanley Aronowitz, Tony Benn, Nick Davies, Daniel C. Dennett
description: Do you shape the world or does it shape you? Drawing on leading thinkers from around the world, and with a torrent of mind-expanding ideas and information, The Lottery of Birth will make you think again about what it means to be free.

title: Copperman
cast: Luca Argentero, Galatea Ranzi, Antonia Truppo
description: Anselmo (Luca Argentero) is a world traveler who has the innocence of a child and the heart of a lion. Abandoned by his father who believed he is a superhero, Anselmo lives with his mother, who has succeeded in convincing him that he is a special kind of human. He resembles Forrest Gump, a grown up with a pure heart, a disarming candor, a childish soul totally free from suspicions.

title: An American Girl Story: Summer Camp, Friends For Life
cast: Zoe Manarel, Alison Fernandez, Lauren Donzis, Camryn Manheim, Monique Green

When the administrator makes them explore nature and confiscates all tech, they think their summer’s doomed. Things take a mysterious turn when they meet Jordan, an enchanting “counselor” who sends them on an adventure, opening them up to a world of possibilities – like befriending Drew.

title: The Omega Code
cast: Casper Van Dien, Michael York, Catherine Oxenberg
description: Ancient codes hidden within the Torah reveal the secrets of global events, past, present, and future. One man is after the Code, seeking the power to change the world as we know it... for the worse. Another seeks the truth, risking his life and everything he stands for in order to stop him.

title: Arthur & Merlin: Knights of Camelot

King Arthur has been absent for five long years, fighting a war that has stricken his knights, left his throne defenceless and his queen at the mercy of Modred. But as he fights to preserve Camelot - the toughest conflict is within himself. Guided by wizard Merlin, Arthur must strive to become the king that his nation needs.

title: The A-List

But when they find the truck is actually filled with stolen gold, the band of brothers realize they've been double-crossed by one of their own - and putting the situation right will be all out war.

title: Touch of Pink
cast: Jimi Mistry, Kyle MacLachlan, Suleka Mathew

title: Severed Ties

title: Tripwire

description: A terrorist (Warner) and an FBI agent (Knox) fight out a personal feud with one another.

Once there, he refuses treatment, instead waiting for his cohorts to break him out. Caught between an obsessed cop and the troubled surgeon assigned to save his life, the hospital is now a taught-and-tense situation that could turn into a bloody battleground at any moment.

title: The Rookies

cast: Joe Azzopardi

Despite the hostility they feel from all sides, a tender romance grows in this inspiring comedy about fitting in.

title: Prisoners of the Sun
cast: John Rhys-Davies, David Charvet, Carmen Chaplin
description: A multinational expedition discovers a lost city beneath a pyramid, where they must stop the reawakened gods of ancient Egypt from initiating the Apocalypse.

Soon, they are joined by their daughter Chelsea (Jane Fonda), her fiancé Bill, and his son Billy. Norman develops a bond with Billy, providing the framework for a summer in which the Thayers' strained relationships are finally allowed to heal.

title: Not Like Everyone Else
cast: Alia Shawkat, Illeana Douglas, Eric Schweig

Diane "Blaze" Sullivan, the host of a nationally televised punk-rock show on New Year's Eve, is receiving calls from a mysterious killer who tells her of his plans to off someone at midnight in each of America's major time zones and she will be the last.

Enjoying a picture-perfect marriage, Spencer becomes the target of a multi-million dollar hit. Now Spencer and Jen are on the run for their lives.
